The paper proposes a novel Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) approach for the classification of raw dry-EEG signals without any data pre-processing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper utilizes the Steady State Visual Evoked Potential (SSVEP) paradigm, which involves visual stimuli, indicating that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the practical application of Brain-Computer Interface (BCI), suggesting that it may belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel CNN architecture, indicating that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
